ons? 4. What are some of the critical elements to consider in designing the assessment and developing the methodology \u2013 e.g. user voices and perceptions rather than an institutional approach? 5. What are critical factors to keep in mind when implementing the questionnaires/focus group discussions i.e. research team, target groups, language, etc.? 6. Which institutions need to be involved in A2J assessments? Are local capacities being built through the assessment? 17:15\u201317:30 End of Day 1 Day 2: Friday, 8 October 2010 8:30\u20139:00 Registration Session IV: Working Group I 9:00\u201310:15 Session Objective: To identify recommendations on developing guidelines for access to justice assessments.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "b832ac70-a954-4897-85ec-d47a0782e056": {"__data__": {"id_": "b832ac70-a954-4897-85ec-d47a0782e056", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/sharing-experience-access-justice-engaging-non-state-justice-systems-conducting-assessments", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Sharing Experience in Access to Justice: Engaging with Non-State Justice Systems & Conducting Assessments", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/sharing-experience-access-justice-engaging-non-state-justice-systems-conducting-assessments", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "807e9b34f115dbda8b52b003b3ed6146d0dc4ab8fd6c74d1a0c651c868ff8543"}, "2": {"node_id": "5f99475c-abe3-4526-bb75-beca788206de", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_